1
00:00:09,967 --> 00:00:11,433
<i>I've been feeling
kind of guilty lately.</i>

2
00:00:11,567 --> 00:00:13,467
<i>It's been a while
since we've did it, you know.</i>

3
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,833
<i> Wrong again! Fix that!</i>

4
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:16,367
<i>Maybe it's been months
since Sir Paolo has gotten any,</i>

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:17,133
<i> that's why he's like that.</i>

6
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,333
<i> You fired one of your staff</i>

7
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:19,667
<i>just because they called you
sexually frustrated?</i>

8
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,300
<i>If you can't do it at home,
then find it somewhere else.</i>

9
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:23,033
<i> I cooked all your favorites.</i>

10
00:00:23,167 --> 00:00:24,033
<i> Please come home early.</i>

11
00:00:24,167 --> 00:00:25,233
<i>That's the oldest trick
in the book.</i>

12
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> No matter how hard you try,</i>

13
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,000
<i>if someone wants to leave,
they'll leave.</i>

14
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:30,167
<i>So you're the husband-and-wife
tandem</i>

15
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,533
<i>- I've heard about.
- No, we're not.</i>

16
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:32,833
<i> Oh, I thought you were.</i>

17
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:34,167
<i> Someone else came first.</i>

18
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:35,833
<i>I'll send you both off this
Friday. Three days out of town.</i>

19
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:37,367
<i>Face to face
with their board.</i>

20
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,567
<i> Sounds like a challenge.</i>

21
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,167
<i> I'm game, if you are.</i>

22
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> Where's the company car?</i>

23
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,333
<i>I canceled it. I thought Oscar
could just drive us.</i>

24
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> Well, Oscar's sick.</i>

25
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:48,200
<i>- How are you getting there?
- No choice. I'll drive.</i>

26
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,600
Hello?

27
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,733
Hon.

28
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,233
Hon?

29
00:00:56,300 --> 00:01:00,167
I'm not comfortable with
the two of you traveling alone.

30
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,000
What do you think of me?

31
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:05,300
That I can't protect myself?

32
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,433
Can you just trust me?

33
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,233
Relax.

34
00:01:11,767 --> 00:01:12,900
Love?

35
00:01:13,033 --> 00:01:14,933
<i>- Love. Easy, slow down.
- Love!</i>

36
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:15,967
Easy.

37
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:17,767
Hi, Marj.

38
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:21,567
Love, your packed meal.
You forgot it.

39
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:22,767
Thank you.

40
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:26,000
Thea, keep an eye
on Paolo, okay?

41
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:30,033
You know how he forgets
to take his vitamins.

42
00:01:30,167 --> 00:01:32,167
- That's too much.
- Of course, Marj.

43
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,100
Don't worry.
I'll take care of Paolo.

44
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:37,233
Thank you.

45
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:39,600
All right then.

46
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,333
Bye.

47
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,400
Bye.

48
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:45,300
I'll see you in three days.

49
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:47,100
- Bye.
- Love you.

50
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,200
- I love you.
- See you.

51
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,367
Okay.

52
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,100
- Bye, Marj.
- Bye.

53
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,033
- Bye.
- See you.

54
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:09,633
I'll see you in three days. Bye!

55
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:11,133
Bye!

56
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:21,000
Deja vu.

57
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,033
This is how you two started,
isn't it?

58
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:26,800
What?

59
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,500
I said I hope
they have a safe trip.

60
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:33,467
It's only three days anyway.

61
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,700
Just like before.

62
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:37,067
I mean, before,

63
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,167
when Paolo would travel.

64
00:02:39,767 --> 00:02:40,500
For work.

65
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,633
The road to La Escondida
is actually really nice.

66
00:03:41,733 --> 00:03:45,133
Feels like the perfect spot
for a breather.

67
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,267
Breather?

68
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:48,967
This is a work trip, Thea.

69
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:52,433
Of course, Boss.

70
00:03:57,333 --> 00:04:02,433
But sometimes we're allowed
to take a little break.

71
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,000
Wow.

72
00:04:13,133 --> 00:04:14,500
It's hot, right?

73
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,600
What's happening?

74
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,133
Great.

75
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:31,567
Just what we need.

76
00:04:36,767 --> 00:04:38,600
Did we stall?

77
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:53,100
Oh, come on!
Why is there no signal?

78
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,033
Now what? It's getting late.

79
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:59,333
Our meeting in La Escondida
is probably waiting for us.

80
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,533
This is hopeless. I've been
trying to fix it for a while.

81
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:04,000
I don't even know
what to do anymore.

82
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:07,300
Do you have a signal?

83
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,100
I've been looking for a signal.

84
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:16,067
- Nothing. Zero bars.
- Oh my God.

85
00:05:17,433 --> 00:05:19,200
My battery's about to die, too.

86
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:25,800
You've got to be kidding me.
Now it's going to rain?

87
00:05:28,467 --> 00:05:30,600
Jobert, look.

88
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:33,267
Oh! I lose again!

89
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,967
Marj!

90
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:40,233
Edward, you're still here?

91
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:43,333
I'm waiting for mom.

92
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:45,100
I ran into Jobert.

93
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:46,500
He asked me to play.

94
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,400
Marj, look.

95
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:51,500
Edward's really good.

96
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:55,333
He now knows how to fix toys.

97
00:05:55,467 --> 00:06:01,733
I told him, when a robot's
broken, don't throw it away.

98
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:04,433
Right, Marj?

99
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:07,367
You said when something
important gets broken,

100
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,400
don't leave it that way.
Fix it first.

101
00:06:15,033 --> 00:06:18,333
Jobert is quoting stuff.

102
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:20,200
Didn't know he was sentimental.

103
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:23,767
It's hard to let go of things.

104
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,933
Where are you?

105
00:06:28,067 --> 00:06:31,533
Come on. I'm just going to look
for someone who can help.

106
00:06:33,133 --> 00:06:34,433
Hello?

107
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:37,233
Anybody there?

108
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,967
- What?
- Nothing. No one's here.

109
00:06:42,133 --> 00:06:43,500
Hello?

110
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:45,367
- We just need shelter!
- Hello?

111
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,000
Hello!

112
00:06:47,133 --> 00:06:48,467
Thea, stay here. Just a second.

113
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,333
Good thing
you still care about Jobert.

114
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,500
Of course. It's Jobert.

115
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,500
That's how it is.

116
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:07,533
When you meet someone like that,

117
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:10,300
it's hard to let go.

118
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:13,200
<i> You don't just forget them.</i>

119
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,367
That kind of concern
doesn't just disappear.

120
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,133
Edward...

121
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,067
What is it?

122
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:29,200
Hello?

123
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:32,733
It's freezing!

124
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:36,900
- Anything?
- Let's go over here.

125
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:37,933
Doesn't seem like
anyone's around.

126
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,400
Come on, let's just
take shelter. Come on.

127
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:41,367
- Where?
- Here. Over here.

128
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,533
Easy. Slow down.

129
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,567
Slow down.

130
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,000
Wait. Hello?

131
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:01,167
Anybody? Slowly.

132
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:02,933
- Come on.
- Over here?

133
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,100
Easy.

134
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:18,400
Marj.

135
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,633
There's water.

136
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,267
<i> The baby's crying.</i>

137
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,467
Marj, I think you're
going into labor.

138
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,900
I'm taking you
to the hospital.

139
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,067
Come on, let's go.

140
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,067
No, no, no.
It's not my due date yet.

141
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,833
- Wait.
- Jobert, call Yolly.

142
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:35,033
- Hurry! Faster, faster!
- Yolly!

143
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:36,333
Marj! Marj!

144
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,067
<i>- Yolly!
- I'll take you to the hospital!</i>

145
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:49,200
I'll just check, okay? Hello?

146
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,533
Anybody home?

147
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,267
Hello?

148
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,100
Looks like no one lives here.

149
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,800
Let's just wait out
the rain here, okay?

150
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,900
It's freezing.

151
00:09:06,933 --> 00:09:08,267
Here's a blanket.

152
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:16,767
Thank you.

153
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:38,033
- Marj.
- Sir! Sir! Sir! Sir!

154
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:41,133
We'll take it from here, Sir.
We've got her. We've got it.

155
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:43,433
Marj!

156
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:11,633
<i> Marj! Marj!</i>

157
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:15,067
She's seven months pregnant.
We need to operate now.

158
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,400
The baby's in distress.

159
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:19,633
Doc, please.
I'm only seven months pregnant.

160
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:20,733
We don't have a choice.

161
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:21,933
If we wait,

162
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:24,133
it'll be more dangerous
for both you and your baby.

163
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:28,833
We've already contacted
your OB for your records.

164
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:30,800
Marj, don't worry.

165
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:32,300
They'll do everything they can,
okay?

166
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:33,400
Just fight.

167
00:10:33,533 --> 00:10:35,333
We'll take care
of your wife now, Sir.

168
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:37,633
- What?
- We'll handle it.

169
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:39,767
I'm not her husband.

170
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:43,433
Where's Paolo?

171
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:45,067
<i> Where's Pao?</i>

172
00:10:46,267 --> 00:10:47,500
Where's the doctor?

173
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:59,433
<i>The number you have dialed
is either unattended...</i>

174
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,667
Paolo, where are you?

175
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,333
Are you okay?

176
00:11:26,433 --> 00:11:28,200
It feels numb.

177
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:31,233
Give it to me. I'll massage it.

178
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:35,433
- You sure?
- Maybe...

179
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:37,667
Maybe it'll ease the pain. Easy.

180
00:11:56,767 --> 00:11:58,333
<i>The number you have dialed
is either unattended...</i>

181
00:11:58,467 --> 00:11:59,133
Where are you guys?

182
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:01,167
<i> Please try your call later.</i>

183
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:11,600
<i> The number you have dialed</i>

184
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:13,500
<i>is either unattended
or out of coverage area.</i>

185
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:14,833
Come on, Paolo.

186
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,133
<i> Please try your call later.</i>

187
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,500
Does it hurt?

188
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,867
I'm going to rotate it, okay?

189
00:12:55,467 --> 00:12:57,700
Marj? Marj.

190
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,100
You're in the recovery room.

191
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,233
Where's my baby?

192
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:05,600
Where's my baby?

193
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,500
Why isn't my baby with me?

194
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:23,467
Your baby is in the
Neonatal Intensive Care Unit.

195
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:26,300
She's very premature.
Only seven months.

196
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:28,867
Right now,
the baby's very fragile.

197
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,100
Is she alive?

198
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,133
She is, but she's critical.

199
00:13:35,267 --> 00:13:38,167
The next 24 hours
are very important.

200
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,500
That's when we'll know
if she'll survive.

201
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,767
I want to see her.

202
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,967
- I want to see my baby.
- Not yet, Marj.

203
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:48,000
Your body's still recovering.

204
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,333
Where's Paolo?

205
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:50,967
- Lie down first.
- Where's Paolo?

206
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,733
I called them.
They're just not answering.

207
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:54,733
I already sent a message.
Just lie down.

208
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:57,333
- Edward, I'm scared.
- This isn't good for your body.

209
00:13:57,467 --> 00:14:00,100
I'm scared I won't be able
to handle this.

210
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:03,633
I need my husband.
Where is my husband?

211
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:06,833
Marj, Marj. Look at me.
Listen to me.

212
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:09,567
Nothing's going to happen
to your baby.

213
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:13,333
She's fighting. So please...

214
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:15,533
you fight too.

215
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,067
I'm here. I'm not leaving you.

216
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,867
I won't abandon you.

217
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,633
Don't think you're alone
in this, okay?

218
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:57,900
I think we passed an auto shop
about two kilometers back.

219
00:14:58,033 --> 00:15:00,500
I'm just going to go back, okay?
Wait for me here.

220
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,567
Paolo, what's the rush?

221
00:15:03,733 --> 00:15:05,300
Stay here with me.

222
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:09,067
Let's not leave yet.

223
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,167
We've done enough.

224
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,733
It's not enough for me.

225
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:17,433
Thea, look.

226
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:22,300
What we did...

227
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,500
is nothing.

228
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:26,000
It was just temptation.

229
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:27,933
It doesn't mean anything.

230
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:29,733
And it should never happen
again.

231
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:35,500
But admit it.

232
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,500
You enjoyed it, didn't you?

233
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:41,067
Why don't we keep going?

234
00:15:42,067 --> 00:15:43,633
No one will ever know.

235
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:46,967
Thea, I have a wife.

236
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:49,533
And you're my brother's
girlfriend.

237
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,200
This is wrong.

238
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:53,033
You shouldn't even be
enjoying this.

239
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,700
What am I? Just someone you use?

240
00:15:57,933 --> 00:16:00,033
Now that you got your release,

241
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,267
you're just going to forget
about me? Just like that?

242
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:04,133
Thea, that's not
what I meant.

243
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:07,300
What I meant is,
this can't ever happen again.

244
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:10,100
What happened in this house
stays in this house.

245
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:12,633
- Do you understand?
- No!

246
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:15,467
You don't get to treat me
like I'm nothing!

247
00:16:28,933 --> 00:16:32,033
I want to see my baby.

248
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:36,167
I want to see my child.

249
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,300
Doctor, please. I'm begging you.

250
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:39,900
Calm down.
Please, Ma'am, calm down.

251
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,067
- We're not going to neglect
- You don't understand.

252
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,733
-your baby.
-I need to make sure she's safe.

253
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:46,400
Where's Paolo?

254
00:16:46,533 --> 00:16:47,467
You'll see your baby.

255
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,867
- Just not right now.
- Where's Paolo?

256
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,200
- I'm calling him.
- Where is Paolo?

257
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:41,100
Please tell your father
we're sorry, okay?

258
00:17:41,233 --> 00:17:43,733
So the house we took shelter
in is yours.

259
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:48,000
<i>We just went in because
the rain was pouring.</i>

260
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:49,633
It's okay, Sir. My dad said so.

261
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:53,733
It's been abandoned
for a long time anyway.

262
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:55,667
Here, this is for the trouble.

263
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,167
Oh no, that's not necessary.

264
00:17:58,433 --> 00:18:00,167
- Thank you.
- It's fine.

265
00:18:07,667 --> 00:18:08,900
Boss, how's it looking?

266
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,800
About two more hours
before it's fixed.

267
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,367
I already sent someone
to buy the part.

268
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:16,633
Okay. We'll just wait.

269
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:19,500
Paolo.

270
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:22,133
Are we not going to talk
about what happened earlier?

271
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:24,833
No. Because there's nothing
to talk about.

272
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,300
Why not?

273
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:29,233
Why do you get to decide?

274
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,267
What about what I want?

275
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:33,533
What else do you want from me?

276
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:35,033
For God's sake, Thea.

277
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:37,033
It was just meaningless sex.

278
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,000
Don't make it into something
bigger than it is.

279
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:48,967
- Hello, Bro.
- Where are you?

280
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:50,900
Why are you only answering now?

281
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:53,967
The car broke down,
then the rain just poured.

282
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,967
<i> Marj gave birth.</i>

283
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,333
She had to undergo surgery
to deliver the baby.

284
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:00,733
Wait, how is that possible?

285
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:02,400
She's only seven months
pregnant.

286
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:04,100
I don't know
what to tell you, Paolo.

287
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,367
Just get back here.

288
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,733
The baby's premature.
She's in the NICU.

289
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:10,233
<i>What are you guys even doing?
Where are you?</i>

290
00:19:10,933 --> 00:19:12,300
I don't know.
I'll figure something out.

291
00:19:12,433 --> 00:19:14,000
I'll get to the hospital
as fast as I can.

292
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,800
Thanks. Bye.

293
00:19:16,533 --> 00:19:18,100
- That was Edward, right?
- Yeah.

294
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:19,533
Marj gave birth.

295
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:22,533
Boss, here's the key.

296
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:25,600
I'll just have my driver
pick it up later.

297
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:29,167
And here's the money
for the part.

298
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:32,700
By any chance, do you have
an extra car we could borrow?

299
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:34,533
Sure.

300
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:37,533
There's one at the end.
You can use that.

301
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:38,833
Thank you.

302
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:40,200
Here's the key.

303
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:42,233
I'll have it returned.
Thank you.

304
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:44,833
The bag.

305
00:19:46,433 --> 00:19:48,533
Can you at least talk to me?

306
00:19:49,467 --> 00:19:51,067
So that's it? Just like that?

307
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:54,467
Hey!

308
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:57,200
Paolo, talk to me!

309
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,633
Paolo!

310
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:39,633
- Love.
- Love.

311
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:41,967
Love.

312
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,500
- I'm sorry, okay?
- It's okay.

313
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:53,233
We didn't know
this would happen.

314
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,700
What matters is you're here now.

315
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:04,267
Love, our baby.

316
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,433
How is she?

317
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:09,400
She's in the NICU right now.

318
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:14,767
I want to see her,
but they won't let me.

319
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:18,933
The doctor said
she can't do that yet.

320
00:21:19,067 --> 00:21:20,833
He's right,
Mr. Torrecampo.

321
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,500
Since your baby is premature,

322
00:21:22,633 --> 00:21:24,333
her lungs
aren't fully developed,

323
00:21:24,467 --> 00:21:26,567
and she's having trouble
breathing.

324
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,567
How long...

325
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:32,967
How long does she have
to stay in the NICU?

326
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,300
<i>We're connecting her
to a ventilator,</i>

327
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,667
<i>and she'll need to stay in the
Neonatal Intensive Care Unit,</i>

328
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:43,067
inside an incubator,
until she reaches full term.

329
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:46,133
That will help her grow stronger
and recover.

330
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:47,767
Excuse me.

331
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:51,100
I feel so bad for our baby.

332
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,333
Love, she'll be okay.

333
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:02,700
She'll be okay. I'll do
everything I can, all right?

334
00:22:02,833 --> 00:22:04,133
Please don't cry.

335
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,467
There.

336
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:29,733
Paolo's old clothes
fit you perfectly.

337
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:32,667
They look so good on you.
Let me see.

338
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:37,600
My handsome boy.

339
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:42,433
I want to look handsome
when I see the baby.

340
00:22:42,567 --> 00:22:43,967
I'm sure you will.

341
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:47,433
The baby's going to be impressed
when she sees you.

342
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:50,267
Oh my.

343
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,533
There!

344
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:54,433
- It fits you perfectly...
- Yolly, where's Oscar?

345
00:22:55,233 --> 00:22:56,100
Ma'am?

346
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,967
Wait a second. Isn't that...

347
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:01,367
Paolo's shirt?

348
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,533
Ma'am, I just got one
of sir's old shirts.

349
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:06,267
The ones he was
going to donate.

350
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:10,267
He wants to come with you
so he can see his niece.

351
00:23:12,433 --> 00:23:14,567
Yolly, don't overstep!

352
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,967
And you, you're not coming.

353
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:19,533
No one's going to take care
of you there,

354
00:23:19,667 --> 00:23:21,733
and your sister won't be able
to watch you.

355
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,400
Ma'am, I can look after him.

356
00:23:25,433 --> 00:23:27,567
What? No!
You'll just cause trouble.

357
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:30,267
It's a hospital, not a party.

358
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,400
And Marj's condition is serious.

359
00:23:32,533 --> 00:23:33,867
You're not coming.

360
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:40,600
And can you please return that
to Paolo?

361
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:43,233
I'm still donating
those for my outreach.

362
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,167
Ma'am?

363
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:46,000
Didn't you hear me?

364
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:48,667
I'm donating those.

365
00:23:58,767 --> 00:23:59,900
That's enough.

366
00:24:03,267 --> 00:24:04,100
It's fine.

367
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:07,433
As long as you're behaving.

368
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:09,133
Right, Jobert?

369
00:24:14,533 --> 00:24:15,300
Dad.

370
00:24:15,433 --> 00:24:17,633
How's my grandchild?
How's Marjorie?

371
00:24:18,667 --> 00:24:19,933
They're both okay now.

372
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:24,233
But the baby's in the NICU.

373
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:29,633
She was born with her body
not yet fully developed.

374
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:30,633
She's premature.

375
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,033
This is your fault, Regina!

376
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,733
You kept stressing Marj out,
and now look what happened!

377
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:40,500
She gave birth too early!

378
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,033
Hold on.

379
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:43,633
It's her fault, too.

380
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:45,233
Instead of staying on bed rest,

381
00:24:45,367 --> 00:24:47,833
she was still taking care
of her sibling.

382
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:49,633
I don't need your excuses!

383
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:55,767
Dad, please. Not here.

384
00:24:56,533 --> 00:25:00,167
If anyone's to blame, it's me.
This is my fault.

385
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,167
Don't be ridiculous.

386
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:03,433
What do you mean
it's your fault?

387
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:10,167
I just feel like...

388
00:25:11,567 --> 00:25:13,500
maybe this is karma
for what I did.

389
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,200
That's why this is happening
to the baby.

390
00:25:19,567 --> 00:25:20,633
What do you mean?

391
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:22,367
What did you do?

392
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:34,167
Hey, Thea.

393
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,700
Your coffee's getting cold.

394
00:25:35,867 --> 00:25:39,000
Paolo's been avoiding me.
Even at work.

395
00:25:39,133 --> 00:25:41,133
Well, he's a new dad.

396
00:25:41,267 --> 00:25:43,300
Maybe he's on paternity leave.

397
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:44,200
No.

398
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:46,033
He's really avoiding me.

399
00:25:46,167 --> 00:25:47,333
You've got Edward anyway.

400
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:49,567
- He's still a Torrecampo.
- Yeah.

401
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:51,733
But he's not the golden boy.

402
00:25:51,867 --> 00:25:53,000
Girl, are you okay?

403
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:55,933
- Friend!
- Congratulations.

404
00:25:56,067 --> 00:25:58,100
You're eight weeks pregnant,
Ms. Villareal.

405
00:25:58,233 --> 00:25:59,633
I couldn't even hug you
last night

406
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:02,167
because Paolo
wouldn't let you go.

407
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:03,167
Because he feels guilty.

408
00:26:03,300 --> 00:26:04,767
Edward, you can't fool me.

409
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:06,300
Forget about Marj.

410
00:26:06,433 --> 00:26:08,933
You don't realize how lucky
you are to have her.

411
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:10,900
Be content with her.

412
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,833
Don't let her go.

413
00:26:12,967 --> 00:26:14,967
You're acting paranoid, Paolo.

414
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:17,633
Are you scared your wife's
going to find out

415
00:26:17,767 --> 00:26:19,667
you're no different from her ex?

416
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:20,967
We already have
so many problems.

417
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:22,800
Don't add to them!

418
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:27,267
What are you two arguing about?
